content.description:
Lynn Larson cleaned this boulder for the 2013 Save Sandstone Festival. Then, it snowed and she never climbed it. In 2014, it has obviously been climbed. By whom? I don't know. If you want to claim an FA or throw out a name, contact me. 

  This problem has been wet on dry days, so be aware before climbing it. Don't climb wet sandstone. Took a guess at the rating too. Posting it now only to make it available. I will revamp this page when I know more about it.
content.location: Along the road down to Robinson Park

content.description: Sit start low left, work up rail to right, find sloper over lip, work feet up, and continue up face to top. Easy exit on back side of boulder.

Along Old Wagon Road going from 123 to Robinson Park are several boulders. Please don't spread out on the road, keep your things in the grass and be considerate and aware of vehicles passing by. 

  Park in the parking lot by the river and walk back up the road. Don't park along the road; it is meant for two way traffic.
